cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.CL. 

The paper deals with multi-task learning in computer vision, specifically in the context of image retrieval tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new module for multi-task learning, which involves optimizing shared parameters and disentangling irrelevant tasks, which suggests that it could be relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper evaluates its approach on two retrieval tasks, which could make it relevant to the sub-categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
